title: ScreenCoach - Parental Control
content: Our kids are tech savvy and ingenious when it comes to work arounds. Screen Coach has helped us manage our children's screen time, finally something that helps curb YouTube addicts! The results have been fantastic. The boys are proactive with helping each other, around the house and more. What else stands out is the customer service. So friendly and responsive. I highly recommend ScreenCoach to any parents looking for an effective way to create a healthier screen time routine!

title: ScreenCoach - Parental Control
content: Screen Coach is a fantastic and comprehensive solution for managing screen time. While the initial setup is complex, once running it's an absolute game-changer for the kids. The support is what truly sets them apart‚Äîthe team is amazing, answering questions quickly and helpfully via chat. I was even impressed when the founder himself organized a call with me for feedback. This level of dedication is rare and speaks volumes about their commitment. Highly recommended!

title: ScreenCoach - Parental Control
content: I highly recommend ScreenCoach! It has been a game changer in my house as a solution for screen-time management. It rewards my girls for doing fun activities away from screens, get some exercise in each day, helps them form good habits, and gets them more motivated to help with chores. And best of all it's easy for me. I don't have to nag them or threaten to turn the wi-fi off in the house.  They just go and do some activities for earning more screentime, then they put the request through.

title: ScreenCoach - Parental Control
content: Wow, an absolute game changer! We have a fairy young boy who has become addicted to screens. All his attention went to electronics, and gradually shifting all his priorities towards them. We tried few mainstream Parental Control software from big tech vendors as well as some leading 3rd party ones. You end up setting up arbitrary limits and end up with an angry child. This allows kids to earn extra screen time, completely changing their behaviour, leaving them feeling trusted and in control.

title: Llama Life ADHD Routine & Task
content: Was using Llama Life first on desktop and then iOS, great to have it on Android. As someone with ADHD who has a demanding work day, being able to use the app to setup my to-do lists has really helped my headspace. My USP for the app is the regular chime to bring attention back to what I'm doing, I have it for three minutes lol. Rain sounds and (seperately) some form of binaural beats are my preferred working method. Devs have been engaged with improving and feedback, a genuine 5 star app.

title: Llama Life ADHD Routine & Task

title: Llama Life ADHD Routine & Task
content: Absolutely loving Llama Life! I've been trying to find my productivity groove for years & finally have it figured out. I'm using Todoist to keep my projects & tasks organized, and Llama Life for my daily focus & getting tasks done - I love that it syncs with my Todoist daily list. I'm using most of the features (background noise, chimes & alarms, morning routine, pomodoro etc..) and am really happy with it all. The price is fair and support is great too.

title: Llama Life ADHD Routine & Task
content: REQUIRES subscription, no full free version. title: Llama Life ADHD Routine & Task

title: The Way: Meditation Path
content: I did the 30-day free trial (no credit card required) & eventually signed up for an annual membership. I heard about it when he was a guest on Micheal B Beckwith's podcast. It simplifies the process & the format just flows really smoothly. Henry Shukman guides you on a journey, introducing a wide array of different meditation techniques to help you deepen your practice & determine which techniques resonate with you the most. His voice is also super calming. Love it, highly recommend!

content: It's clear that the people who made this understand ND brains, fully. The app is pleasing to look at and use, without being overwhelming. title: Inflow ADHD
content: Highly recommend for those with ADD/ADHD - a safe place to land where you will feel understood (at last!) and learn ways of adapting for your personal success, and not someone else's version.

title: Inflow ADHD
content: An app specific to my ADHD needs is a godsend. I have been looking for something to help me manage my ADHD for a long time and I finally found something that knows how to put it in small sections so I don't forget or overlooked things. I am also not overwhelmed with having to do long list of goals or even simple goals that have nothing to do with my ADHD and become a nuisance. Inflow give me exactly what I need and for that reason I'm finding it worth the money.

title: Inflow ADHD

title: Inflow ADHD
content: I am really enjoying this app. Although it has not become an ingrained routine yet, I have spent more time in this app than any other app for people with ADHD. Why is that? Because it really is making a difference. I am learning skills and tasks that I've never considered before. Each one building on the other. I actually have hope which is a big key to resilience. And nothing changes if nothing changes, right? It feels so empowering to have tools to access to hack your way to a better life.

title: Inflow ADHD
content: It's actually genuinely interesting - and not dumbed down or patronising.

title: Inflow ADHD
content: I never write these reviews, but I felt others should know. Only way out is finding the login site through a proper browser on the phone or on the computer. Also the voice acting is bad.

title: Parental Control App: Mobicip
content: I use Mobicip for my family's Dell laptop. It is VERY effective. Only my user profile is an admin, not my kids' profiles. My kids prefer the Brave browser which offers an Incognito mode and a Tor option so you have to update the policies in your laptop's registry (easier than it sounds) to disable those for their accounts, otherwise Mobicip (and Qustodio, et al) will be defeated. But once you disable Tor and Incognito, then Mobicip is very effective. Highly recommend!

title: Parental Control App: Mobicip
content: While Microsoft Family and Google Family Link work just fine, they are restricted to their own companies. Mobicip bridges the gap by applying the same settings per person on any device it has hbeen installed on. Simple to setup, easy to use, and quite informative on your child's activities, Mobicip has maintained my sanity (for 3 kids) with the knowledge that my children's exposure to "overt" and downright dangerous items is significantly reduced. A recommendation for all parents in the digital age.

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: So I have timeblindness (the curse of ADHD) and have been looking for an app exactly like this for ages! To be able to list a bunch of tasks and then schedule them directly to my day by timeblocks is exactly what I've been looking for. The focus timer is a helpful touch I didn't know I needed either. Some pointers. It would be good if I could customise the titles in my lists (essentials, nicetodos), maybe add some more, oh and if there was a 24hr time format. Love it. Keep up the good work

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: I wanted to love the app but I don't really. It has potential but currently it does not live up to it. It's supposed to reschedule unfinished tasks and send notifications for various reasons. It does not. It seems to seems to be just a basic to do list app were I can save multiple to-do lists. I have already paid to have the app for a year so I am hoping improvements will be made.

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: pretty much unusable without a subscription due to hilariously low limits.

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: Great idea; I got the app to help manage my routine (and ADHD!). I'm still getting used to the app right now, and when I try to do certain things (duplicate a task) the app suggests I get a free trial or upgrade my account. EDIT: A separate bug issue was resolved very quickly by the developers and I appreciate their prompt response. I have increased my rating, and will do so again if I get on well with the app features!

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: as someone who's is genuinely interested in the entrepreneurial lifestyle and is also a procrastinator. This app has been a huge help for me to tackle tasks without feeling overwhelmed, stressed, or left with anxiety. I'm able to knock off tasks and feel extremely good about myself, knowing I'm on route to accomplish my goals! I would absolutely recommend it to anyone who is looking to keep themselves on track. solid tool! cheers, guys!

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: Love this app!! I can't remember a time I was this productive! Very easy to use! Time blocking is great for helping me manage my time and what can be achieved throughout the day! Alarms not invasive and can be snoozed easily, if you need a little time. Stops my procrastination and no longer overwhelmed with all my daily tasks. Especially like the option to assign tasks either essential or nice to do,plus task focus. Thanks!!

content: Absolute garbage. Dont trust this app. It glitches and it has no way of syncing your tasks if you have to uninstall, loose your phone etc. I lost hundreds of tasks and im very stressed now. title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: I love this app. I tried others and this is the best. The interface is clean and I love the separate tasklist that you can schedule from in the timeline. I also like that it visually shows each empty block on the timeline. It helps with my ADHD. The rescheduling feature is nice as well. I really wish it had the ability to drag and drop tasks within the timeline. I end up shuffling tasks around a lot and it's tedious. If it had that feature I would be willing to pay for it.

title: Yoodoo: ADHD Daily Planner
content: Above and beyond the alternatives! I downloaded and tried many different apps and this is the only one I immediately took to. You can create timed and untimed tasks and subtasks, which enables you to track progress flexibly- some days I may do all my weekly chores in 1 day, other weeks it takes days, and this app gives me the flexibility to track both (others don't!). It also has a focus feature to help task management, can import your calendar, & the developer is really receptive to feedback
